{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c437ace5-31d2-4938-844e-3f11a41c1e56","content":"Analyzing .NET crash dumps is outside the scope of my available tools (the `dump-collect` skill only covers **collecting** dumps, not analyzing them). However, here's how you can investigate:\n\n**Using `dotnet-dump analyze`** (cross-platform):\n```bash\ndotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump\ndotnet-dump analyze your-file.dmp\n```\nUseful SOS commands inside the analyzer:\n| Command | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `clrstack` | Managed call stack |\n| `pe` (PrintException) | Last exception details |\n| `dumpheap -stat` | Heap summary |\n| `threads` | List all threads |\n| `clrstack -all` | Stacks for all threads |\n\n**Using Visual Studio** (Windows):\n- Open the `.dmp` file directly → click **\"Debug with Managed Only\"**.\n\n**Using `lldb` + SOS** (Linux/macOS):\n```bash\nlldb --core your-file.dmp\nplugin load libsosplugin.so\nclrstack\npe\n```\n\nA typical workflow: run `pe` first to see if there's an unhandled exception, then `clrstack` to get the call stack at the crash point.\n\nWant help setting up any of these tools?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"6b1f485d-be72-45a3-997e-b709a2482666","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about analyzing a .dmp crash dump file. Let me check the available skills - there's a `dump-collect` skill, but its description specifically says:\n\n- USE FOR: enabling automatic crash dumps, capturing dumps, setting up dump collection\n- DO NOT USE FOR: analyzing or debugging dumps, post-mortem investigation with lldb/windbg/dotnet-dump analyze\n\nSo the dump-collect skill is NOT appropriate here. The user wants to analyze a dump, not collect one.\n\nLet me provide guidance on analyzing .NET crash dumps directly.","outputTokens":441,"requestId":"DA15:AAEEE:5C2326:68D3AE:6A03DA59"},"id":"96fd32a9-b3ba-43f4-bbdd-ced794fe90b4","timestamp":"2026-05-13T01:56:59.540Z","parentId":"89b00276-3d73-47f2-b632-e55819b45e77"}
